Description: THE WADSWORTH CENTER (WC) RABIES LABORATORY WILL PERFORM TESTING TOSUPPORT THE USDA WILDLIFE SERVICES (USDA-WS) ORAL RABIES VACCINATION(ORV) CAMPAIGN FOR THE CONTROL AND SURVEILLANCE OF TERRESTRIAL RABIES.EFFORTS TO ELIMINATE THE SPREAD OF RABIES OUTBREAKS IN WILDLIFE AREINITIATED AND MANAGED BY STAFF FROM THE USDA WILDLIFE SERVICES. USDA-WSDISTRIBUTES BAITS CONTAINING A RABIES VACCINE IN AREAS THROUGHOUT THE USPREDETERMINED BY EVALUATING ECOLOGICAL AND EPIDEMIOLOGICAL FACTORS OFWILDLIFE RABIES. ORV BAITS ARE DESIGNED TO ELICIT AN IMMUNE RESPONSEAGAINST RABIES IN ANIMALS THAT CONSUME THE BAITS. WHEN THESE ANIMALS AREEXPOSED TO RABIES, THE EXPECTATION IS THAT THE IMMUNE RESPONSE WILLDECREASE THE RISK OF INFECTION, THEREBY PREVENTING THE SPREAD OF THEDISEASE.

Description: AWARD DESCRIPTIONRECIPIENT NAME:UNIVERSITY OF MINNESOTA CENTER FOR ANIMAL HEALTH AND FOOD SAFETYPROJECT CONTACT - ANDRES PEREZPROGRAM MANAGER:PRIMARY: COLE F. THISIS WHAT THE GS WILL ENTER IN THE AWARD DESCRIPTION FIELD IN EFG.AWARD PURPOSE: TO EXPLORE AND DETERMINE APPROPRIATENESS OF NOVEL EARLYDISEASE DETECTION METHODS FOR SWINE FADS TO ENHANCE THE CURRENT PASSIVESURVEILLANCE APPROACHES PRIMARILY UTILIZED TO HELP DETECT FOREIGN ANIMALDISEASE (FAD) INCURSION. TO EXPAND DATA AND INFORMATION SHARING NETWORKSAMONG THE SWINE INDUSTRY, STATE, TRIBAL, AND FEDERAL PARTNERS TO SUPPORTEARLY DETECTION AND RAPID RESPONSE GOALS. THIS WORK WILL INFORM FUTUREVS DIRECTION IN DISEASE DETECTION METHODS AND IMPROVE NATIONAL DISEASESURVEILLANCE PLANS. IT WILL ALSO SUPPORT DISEASE OUTBREAK PREPAREDNESSAND RESPONSE EFFORTS, SHOULD ONE OF THE THREE FADS (FOOT AND MOUTHDISEASE, AFRICAN SWINE FEVER, OR CLASSICAL SWINE FEVER) BE DETECTED INTHE U.S.ACTIVITIES TO BE PERFORMED: THROUGH QUALITATIVE METHODS, SUCH ASSTAKEHOLDER AND POLICY MAPPING, THE RECIPIENT WILL DESCRIBE CURRENTPROCESSES FOR IDENTIFICATION AND REPORTING OF FAD SUSPECTS PREVALENT INTHE U.S. SWINE INDUSTRY. THIS WILL INCLUDE AN EVALUATION OF THE STATUSOF PROCESSES FOR IDENTIFYING AND SUBMITTING FAD SUSPECTS AND THE DESIGNOF POTENTIAL APPROACHES FOR IMPROVED SURVEILLANCE FOR EARLY DETECTION.DELIVERABLES AND EXPECTED OUTCOMES:THERE ARE 3 DELIVERABLES REQUESTED.FIRST, A REPORT SUMMARIZING THE STRENGTHS, WEAKNESSES, OPPORTUNITIES,AND THREATS ASSOCIATED WITH THE FOLLOWING.1) INDUSTRY APPLICATION OF PROTOCOLS AND STANDARD OPERATING PROCEDURESUSED BY THE THREE NATIONAL ANIMAL HEALTH LABORATORY NETWORK (NAHLN)LABORATORIES THAT CONCENTRATE PROCESSING OF MOST SWINE SAMPLES IN THECOUNTRY.2) PROCESSES USED BY SWINE FARMS TO IDENTIFY FAD SUSPECTS INCLUDINGFACTORS ASSOCIATED WITH THEIR GEOGRAPHICAL AND SYSTEM DISTRIBUTION,FACTORS ASSOCIATED WITH PASSIVE SURVEILLANCE AND CURRENT TRIGGERS FORACTIVE SURVEILLANCE.3) IT SYSTEMS TO COLLECT AND SUMMARIZE SWINE PRODUCTION DATA INCLUDINGMETRICS OF THEIR USE AND DISTRIBUTION BY THE INDUSTRY AND THE POTENTIALLINK WITH SETTING ALARMS FOR EARLY DETECTION OF FADS.SECOND, A REPORT DESCRIBING THE POTENTIAL FOR INCENTIVES TO SUPPORTNOVEL SURVEILLANCE APPROACHES DEVELOPED IN COLLABORATION WITH THE U.S.SWINE INDUSTRY. EXAMPLES OF POTENTIAL NOVEL SURVEILLANCE APPROACHESMIGHT INCLUDE IMPLEMENTATION SYSTEMS TO QUICKLY DIFFERENTIATE ENDEMICDISEASES FROM FADS, OR TARGETED SURVEILLANCE OF HIGH-RISK EVENTS.THIRD, A PROOF OF PRINCIPLE DOCUMENT FOR PILOTING THE IMPLEMENTATION OFSURVEILLANCE APPROACHES THAT LEVERAGE ROUTINELY COLLECTED SWINEPRODUCTION DATA. EXAMPLES MAY INCLUDE AUTOMATED ANOMALY DETECTIONMETHODS THAT MAY TRIGGER THE IDENTIFICATION AND SUBMISSION OF A SUSPECTFAD. THIS INFORMATION WILL BE USED TO IDENTIFY OPPORTUNITIES FORCAPACITY BUILDING EFFORTS RELATED TO EARLY DISEASE DETECTION.INTENDED BENEFICIARY(IES): U.S. SWINE INDUSTRY, USDA APHIS VETERINARYSERVICESSUBRECIPIENT ACTIVITIES, IF KNOWN OR SPECIFIED AT THE TIME OF AWARD: NOTAPPLICABLE

Description: 1.AWARD PURPOSE. THE PURPOSE OF THIS AGREEMENT IS TO COMPLETE PROACTIVE RISK ASSESSMENTS (RAS) FOR THE MOVEMENT OF FISH FROM FARMS AND HATCHERIES TO NATURAL WATERS FOR STOCKING OR TO OTHER FISH FARMS WHERE SUSCEPTIBLE SPECIES MAY OR MAY NOT BE PRESENT DURING A VIRAL HEMORRHAGIC SEPTICEMIA OUTBREAK. THESE RAS WILL PROVIDE CONCRETE SCIENTIFIC EVIDENCE FOR STATE, TRIBAL, AND FEDERAL ANIMAL EMERGENCY PERSONNEL FOR USE IN THEIR FOREIGN ANIMAL DISEASE (FAD) CONTROL PLANS, WHILE IMPLEMENTING NATIONALLY CONSISTENT DECISIONS ON RISKS AND MOVEMENT OF FISH IN AN OUTBREAK. 2.ACTIVITIES TO BE PERFORMED. A. ENGAGE FISH STAKEHOLDERS OF THE GREAT LAKES REGION COMMERCIAL AND NATURAL FISHERY SECTORS THROUGH THE FORMATION OF A WORKGROUP COMPOSED OF FISH HEALTH EXPERTS, FEDERAL,STATE, AND TRIBAL NATION REGULATORY AGENCIES AND PRODUCERS, AS WELL ASPRIVATE PRODUCERS; B. CHARACTERIZE FISH TARGET SPECIES PRODUCTION, AS WELL AS MOVEMENT FOR STOCKING INTO NATURAL WATERS; C. CONDUCT ASSESSMENTS OF THE RISK OF FISH FINGERLINGS AND MATURE STOCKING FISH MOVEMENTS IN A VHS OUTBREAK FROM FARMS AND HATCHERIES FOR STOCKING INTO NATURAL WATERS OR OTHER FISH FARMS WHERE SUSCEPTIBLE SPECIES MAY OR MAYNOT BE PRESENT; D. TRANSLATE RAS INTO MOVEMENT GUIDANCES FOR REGULATORS; E. REVIEW STATE AND TRIBAL REGULATORY VHS REQUIREMENTS/RESPONSE PLANS ACROSS THE GREAT LAKES REGION AND COMPARE TO PROPOSED MOVEMENT GUIDANCES; F. CREATE FISH PRODUCER DIRECT-ACTION GUIDES AND CONDUCT OUTREACH TO STAKEHOLDERS. 3.DELIVERABLES AND EXPECTED OUTCOMES. DELIVERABLES: A. AN ESTABLISHED SECURE FINFISH SUPPLY (SFFS) WORKGROUP THAT IS COMMITTED TO THE COMPLETION OF THE RAS; B. AN UNDERSTANDING HOW FISH ARE PRODUCED AND MOVED, WHICH WILL HELP US TO IDENTIFY COMMONALITIES IN MOVEMENTS, THUS PROVIDING THE SCOPE FOR THE RAS. WE PLAN TO PUBLISH THE FINDINGS FOR THIS OBJECTIVE; C. RISK ASSESSMENTS -INCLUDING DISEASE SPREAD MODELING - OF THE MOVEMENT OF FISH FINGERLINGS AND MATURE STOCKING FISH IN A VHS OUTBREAK FROM FARMS AND HATCHERIES FOR STOCKING INTO NATURAL WATERS OR OTHER FISH FARMS WHERE SUSCEPTIBLE SPECIES MAY OR MAY NOT BE PRESENT; D. MOVEMENT GUIDANCE DOCUMENTS FOR REGULATOR USE DURING A VHS OUTBREAK; E. A LAY PUBLICATION FOR COMMERCIAL AQUACULTURE AND FISHERY ASSOCIATIONS JOURNALS/NEWSLETTERS AND FISH EXTENSION WEBSITES IN WHICH WE PROVIDE THE REASONING FOR THE RECOMMENDATIONS IN THE MOVEMENT GUIDANCE; F. DEDICATED SECURE FINFISH SUPPLY (SFFS) WEBSITE WHERE AQUATIC LIVESTOCK PRODUCERS AND TRIBAL NATION, STATE, AND FEDERAL HATCHERY PRODUCERS AND REGULATORY AGENCIES CAN ACCESS RAS AND TRANSLATED INFORMATION ON RA APPLICATION IN MOVEMENT GUIDANCE DOCUMENTS AND DIRECT-ACTION GUIDES. PRESENTATION OF ONGOINGUPDATES ON RA PROGRESS AND OUTCOMES AT THE JOINT USAHA/AAVLD AQUACULTURE COMMITTEE MEETING, THE AVMA'S AQUATIC VETERINARY MEDICINE COMMITTEE, THE AQUACULTURE AMERICA CONFERENCE, AND THE INTERNATIONAL SYMPOSIUM ON AQUATIC ANIMAL HEALTH. SPECIFIC OUTREACH TO STAKEHOLDERS FROM DESTINATION AND SOURCE TRADE PARTNER STATES AND TRIBAL NATIONS; WE WILL CONVENE THESE STAKEHOLDERS IN A SEPARATE MEETING DURING THE AQUACULTURE AMERICA 2023 CONFERENCE. EXPECTED OUTCOMES: THE WORKGROUP WILL BE THE FOUNDATION FOR CONSENSUS AMONG DIFFERING AGENCIES, AND THE SCIENCE-BASED RAS, MOVEMENT GUIDANCES, AND DIRECT-ACTION GUIDES WILL FACILITATE THE MOVEMENT OF FISH IN COMMERCE DURING A LARGE-SCALE FISH DISEASE OUTBREAK,NAMELY VHS IN THE GREAT LAKES, WHILE CONCURRENTLY CONTROLLING DISEASE SPREAD. THIS WORK WILL BE THE SPRING BOARD FOR FUTURE RAS ON ADDITIONAL FISH DISEASES, SPECIES, AND REGIONS. 4.INTENDED BENEFICIARY(IES). COMMERCIAL FISH PRODUCERS; STATE, FEDERAL, AND TRIBAL NATION HATCHERIES; STATE, TRIBAL, AND FEDERAL EMERGENCY MANAGEMENT PERSONNEL AND REGULATORS; FISH HEALTH PROFESSIONALS AND VETERINARIANS; U.S. FISH CONSUMERS. 5.SUBRECIPIENT ACTIVITIES. N/A
